───────────────────────────────────────
EXTRACTION TASK
───────────────────────────────────────

1. MAIN KEYWORD (1)
   - The single most important keyword for this content
   - Best balance of search volume (> 100/month) and achievable difficulty (20–70)
   - Must be included in primary_keywords

2. PRIMARY KEYWORDS (3–5, including main_keyword)
   - Include metadata: search_volume, difficulty_score, relevance_score
   - Prioritize keywords with good volume/difficulty ratio

3. SECONDARY KEYWORDS (5–10)
   - Supporting keywords with high relevance; include semantic variations
   - Include metadata with search_volume and difficulty_score

4. LSI KEYWORDS (5–10)
   - Semantically related terms for content depth
   - Terms that frequently co-occur with primary keywords

5. LONG-TAIL KEYWORDS (5–8)
   - Specific, question-based opportunities ("how to...", "best... for...")
   - Include geographic or modifier variations if relevant

6. KEYWORD DENSITY ANALYSIS
   - Calculate current density for each primary keyword
   - Target: 1–3% for primary, 0.5–1% for secondary
   - Identify placement locations (title, H1, first paragraph, headings, conclusion)

7. SEARCH INTENT CLASSIFICATION
   - Classify as: informational / transactional / navigational / commercial

8. KEYWORD DIFFICULTY
   - Numeric score 0–100 for each keyword
   - Flag keywords with difficulty > 70 as "challenging"

9. SEARCH VOLUME ESTIMATES
   - Realistic monthly estimates; mark low-volume keywords (< 100/month)

10. KEYWORD CLUSTERS
    - Group related keywords by topic/thematic similarity
    - Provide cluster_name, keywords, primary_keyword, topic_theme

11. OPTIMIZATION RECOMMENDATIONS
    - Specific actions to improve keyword performance
    - Content gaps to fill; keyword placement suggestions

12. SEARCH VOLUME SUMMARY
    - Total estimated monthly volume by category: primary, secondary, long_tail
